{"name": "loc-lines", "metadata": {"name": "loc-lines", "version": "0.1.2", "classifiers": ["Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A small CLI tool that will tell you the number of lines that a file or directory has.", "upload_time": 1732660270}, "documentation": ["# loc-lines\r\n\r\nLines Of Code is a command-line tool that tells you how many lines a file or children of a directory have.\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\n```shell\r\npip install loc-lines\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Usage\r\n\r\nTo read a file, simply use the command:\r\n```shell\r\npy -m loc \\path\\to\\file\r\n```\r\nWant to include whitespace in the response?:\r\n```shell\r\npy -m loc \\path\\to\\file -w\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo read a directory filled with files do:\r\n```shell\r\npy -m loc \\path\\to\\dir .txt .py\r\n```\r\nThe trailing file extensions specify which extensions to include in your response.\r\nEx. If a directory has three files, a .txt, a .py, and a .java, lines will only be read from the first two.\r\n\r\nTo search all sub directory's:\r\n```shell\r\npy -m loc \\path\\to\\dir -s .txt .py\r\n```\r\nSpecify the option -s to search all sub directory's of the selected directory\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "loc.cli", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "loc.cli.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "loc.read", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "loc.read.path_exts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "loc.read.get_ext", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "loc.read.get_dir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dir", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "sub", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "exts", "type": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "loc.read.get_lines", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "ws", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "loc.read.ws_text", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ws", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "loc.read.read_dir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dir", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": 